        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 6:57PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Galatia, or near Harrisburg, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrisburg, Eldorado, Galatia, Raleigh, and Muddy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
